<p>Hmm - also if you're not only interested in horror:</p>
<p>Baen (and some other publishers) have part of their catalog available for free here:<br />
<a href="http://www.baen.com/library/">http://www.baen.com/library/</a><br />
and here<br />
<a href="http://www.webscription.net/c-1-free-library.aspx">http://www.webscription.net/c-1-free-library.aspx</a></p>
<p>And speaking of Baen, some of you know that they release CDs occasionally with their hardcover books.<br />
The files are legally available for free here:<br />
<a href="http://baencd.thefifthimperium.com/">http://baencd.thefifthimperium.com/</a></p>
<p>(I should say there is SOME horror sprinkled in there, but most of that is &quot;Dark Fantasy&quot; so don't expect a lot of creepypasta.)</p>

